results.lead_paragraph: So far as history reports, Dr. Samuel Johnson acted only once (in the matter of the Cock Lane ghost) as a private eye. In 1944 Lillian de la Torre realized happily that Johnson possessed every trait of character and intellect of the Great Detective of fiction, and began setting down a series of his detectival exploits, narrated, of course, as from the pen of James Boswell.
